# Force LF line endings in the repo for all text files; let git auto-detect text vs binary.
# Keeps Windows working trees as CRLF (when client has core.autocrlf=true) while making
# the repo+index consistently LF — independent of any consumer's git config. Prevents
# environment-dependent phantom diffs (e.g., Cowork/WSL viewing CRLF working tree against
# LF HEAD as many "modified" files).
* text=auto eol=lf
